6.13	We recommended the Local Chief Executive to: 

a. Request for the allocation of budget for the procurement of the materials and equipment necessary for the immediate operation of the water reservoirs;

b. Strictly adhere to the timelines of the implementation of the projects to achieve the desirable socio-economic development for the benefit of the residents of El Salvador City;

c. Direct the GSO to cause the issuance of ICS/PAR to the barangay end-users of the solar streetlights; and 

d. Direct the BAC to require the suppliers to issue warranty security for all PPAs.

Instruct the Acting Municipal Treasurer to fully maximize the use of the system and to:
a. Require the liquidating officer and all accountable officers to make certain that all collections are entered into the system and reconcile the cashbook maintained with E-TRACS regularly;
b. Require system enhancement to patch any glitches to be able to generate the desired complete and accurate reports; 
c. Ensure constant maintenance check on the system’s software and hardware requirements.

We recommended that Management revisit the accounting and reporting guidelines on the local roads management system as prescribed by COA Circular No. 2015-008 dated November 23, 2015 and ––

a. Direct the General Services Officer to coordinate with the City Planning and Development Officer as well as the City Engineer to update the City’s current road map to facilitate the preparation of proper inventory and reporting of the City’s Road Network Systems and likewise prepare the Report on Local Road Networks as presented in Annex A;

b. Instruct the City Accountant to coordinate with the General Service Officer in the reconciliation of records and likewise maintain separate subsidiary ledgers for the road networks and their corresponding components (road lot, road pavement, drainage and slope protection structures, and other miscellaneous structures) and such ledgers shall be maintained for each local road. Also, require the same to prepare the Local Road Network Ledger Cards (LRNLC) to serve as a basis in preparing the lapsing schedule of road network systems and likewise provide additional disclosures in the Notes to Financial Statements as presented;

c. Require the City Engineer to provide the GSO and the City Accounting Office with the complete description and cost segregation of the road components as well as an assessment of their estimated useful lives as it serves as a basis for the latter for valuing the road network items and computing the depreciation of its components;

d. Direct the members of the Inventory Committee to coordinate with the City Planning and Development Officer in conducting the inventory of local roads under the jurisdiction of the City Government and likewise prepare the Report on Physical Count of Road Network Systems to be submitted to the Office of the Auditor for review and evaluation; and

e. Require the City Accountant to adjust the erroneous application of depreciation expense through the road lot components by effecting the following entry:

Dr. Accumulated Depreciation–Road Networks  
P 315,591
Cr. Prior Period Adjustments	
P 315,591

